@node Introduction
@chapter Introduction

Pimacs is an Emacs client for @uref{https://pi.dev/, Pi Coding Agent}.
It provides an interactive interface to the Pi Coding Agent directly
from Emacs.

@node Setup
@chapter Setup

@section Install the Pimacs Agent

First, install the Pimacs agent using npm:

@example
npm install -g --ignore-scripts @@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent
@end example

Then start Pimacs and run @code{/login} to configure your provider:

@example
pi
@end example

@section Install @code{pimacs.el}

Add the following to your Emacs configuration:

@lisp
(use-package pimacs
  :ensure t
  :vc (:url "git@@github.com:ananthakumaran/pimacs.el.git"
       :rev :newest)
  :commands (pimacs-chat))
@end lisp

@node Usage
@chapter Usage

Run @kbd{M-x pimacs-chat} from any file in your project to start a Pimacs chat
session.  Use a prefix argument (@kbd{C-u M-x pimacs-chat}) to start
multiple chats on the same project.

The chat buffer is read-only except for the prompt input area.  Use
@kbd{RET} to submit a prompt and @kbd{C-j} to insert a newline.  Press
@kbd{i} from anywhere in the chat buffer to move point to the prompt
input area.

